es slightly and slapped them. The thought suddenly occurred to me that, who knows, maybe he was saying all this (disguised him … wanted him to pass for someone else) with a certain secret design, that maybe he was sent to spy … and again fury possessed me, but glancing at his foolishly beaming wrinkles, I controlled myself, pretended to laugh; he waved his hands very contentedly and at last, at last, left me in peace.

In spite of a grotesque resemblance to Rascalnikov—No, that’s wrong. 